709374f.text:
Sixth Avenue, at the N. W. corner of W. 18th Street, showing details of the "El" atairway leading to the Downtown platform.
1938-9
Rlexander Alland
This photo is one of a series that appeared in the published volume "Portrait of N. Y." by Feliw Reisenberg and Alex. Alland, IRGV.

709376f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, east side, north from West 18th Street, showing prominently the former Seigel-Cooper Department Store building. This occupies the entire frontage of the 18th to 19th Streets block. Above same are additional former retail establishments. These were Alexanders and Cammeyers. Beyond is the office building, No. 7. W. 23rd Street that contains the Masonic Temple. The Empire State
Building at 34th Street overshadows this structure.
Viiew 2 emphasises the Seigel-Cooper building. This in its
day was one of the outstanding stores of the city.
V.PW NE 1123  View 1: October 28, 1939
View 2: Tay 1940
P. L. Sperr  Veew2. Neg we a76
6h Ave. from roof at n.w. cor. 192 St.
Neg. A-10  July 1, 1941
D 1  .. SErr, photographer

709377f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 18th Street, showing the shopping center of this date (1900's). At the right is Siegel-Coopers Department Store, occupying the 18th to 19th Streets frontage. This feature is emphasired in the later view. In the block beyond are Alexanders and Cammeyers stores. Note the absence of the 'El' in the
limited perspective.
No. 1: May 1906
2: 1940
George L. Balgue
Ne;. 2331
Gedrge D. Chinn
